-- Japan, U.S., EU Reach Broad Agreement on Measures to Fight Counterfeiting
-- B y   C h r i s   C o o p e r
-- 2010-10-02T08:41:38Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-02/japan-u-s-eu-reach-broad-agreement-on-measures-to-fight-counterfeiting.html
Japanese, U.S. and European Union
officials reached a preliminary agreement on anti-counterfeiting
measures to prevent the trade of fake items hindering global
economic growth, Japan’s Ministry of Economy, Trade and Industry
said in a statement in Tokyo today.  The agreement, which didn’t include China, was decided
during a 10-day meeting that ended in Tokyo today, according to
the ministry.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Chris Cooper in Tokyo at 
